headline: General Dynamics awarded $1.07B Navy contract modification
summary: General Dynamics (GD) was awarded a not-to-exceed $1.07B undefinitized contract action modification to a previously awarded contract for long lead time material associated with the Virginia-class Block VI submarines. Work is expected to be completed by September 2035. FY25 shipbuilding and conversion funds in the amount of $1.07B will be obligated at time of award and will not expire at the end of the current fiscal year. Naval Sea Systems Command is the contracting activity. Published first on
